# wbw-spacex-mars-cn — Taste Rules

**Reference DNA**: Vercel (primary — engineering clarity, restraint) + Stripe (secondary — long-form body rhythm, accent rationing).
**Source audit**: `docs/taste-rules.md` (repo root) + TASTE-2A audit.

---

## Identity

Long-form Chinese-language essay (a Wait But Why translation). Typography-first reading experience. The interface disappears when the reader is engaged. Dark editorial theme only — light theme is wrong for long-form reading.

## Color tokens (must use these; never hardcode hex outside `:root`)

```
--bg: #0a0e1a
--bg-soft: #111727
--bg-card: #161e2e
--text: #e6edf3
--text-dim: #8a96a8
--text-mute: #5b6577
--text-muted: #94a3b8
--accent: #4a8cff                (links, active, focus, glassmorphic card tint)
--accent-2: #c1440e              (ONE-TIME scarcity glow; ≤ 1 element)
--accent-3: #ffb347              (tertiary, sparingly)
--border: #232c40
--link: #5aa6ff
--shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(0,0,0,.4)
--shadow-card: 0 0 0 1px rgba(74,140,255,0.18)   (Vercel-style border-shadow)
--status-ok: #4ade80
--status-warn: #fbbf24
--status-fail: #f87171
--warn-bg: #fef3c7
--warn-border: #f59e0b
--warn-text: #92400e
--earth-from: #6cb0ff
--earth-to: #1e5a99
--mars-from: #c1440e
--mars-to: #5a1a08
```

## Radius tokens (must use these)

```
--radius: 8px                     (default card / button)
--radius-sm: 4px                  (small UI: annotation hint, roadmap tag)
--radius-lg: 12px                 (panels: annotated mode, image-fallback)
--radius-card: 14px               (source cards, footnote groups, article figures)
--radius-pill: 999px              (nav tags, footnote refs)
```

## Accent rationing (mandatory)

`--accent` / `#4a8cff`: links, buttons, `:focus-visible`, interactive card tints, active section nav pills.
`--accent-2` / `#c1440e`: **EXACTLY ONE** element per page (scarcity signal). The current usage is a 60px wide glow on one card.
`--accent-3` / `#ffb347`: sparingly.

Never: section headers in accent, dividers in accent, decorative icons in accent, multiple orange elements.

Before merging, `grep -rE '#c1440e' projects/wbw-spacex-mars-cn/styles.css` must be ≤ 1 (within `:root` definition only).

## Accessibility (MANDATORY — do NOT remove)

1. **`:focus-visible` outline rule** — 2px solid `var(--accent)`, 2px offset, `var(--radius-sm)` border-radius.
2. **`prefers-reduced-motion` block** — kills all transitions, animations, and the starfield canvas animation when user has reduced-motion set.

If you remove or weaken either rule, you are violating WCAG 2.4.7 (Focus Visible) or WCAG 2.3.3 (Animation from Interactions). Don't do it.

## Typography

- Font family: `-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", system-ui, "PingFang SC", "Hiragino Sans GB", "Microsoft YaHei", "Noto Sans CJK SC", sans-serif`
- 2 font families only: system sans + `JetBrains Mono` (for code/special callouts). No web fonts.
- Hero H1: 80px / 800 weight / -1.6px tracking
- H2: 24px / 700
- Body: 17.28px / 400 / 1.95 line-height (immersive mode) — the long-form reading rhythm from Stripe

## Anti-patterns (always forbidden)

- Hero photography
- Light theme (use `data-theme="mars-sand"` only as opt-in toggle)
- Multi-color accent inflation
- `filter: drop-shadow(...)`
- Border-style shadows outside annotated mode (they disappear on dark)
- Web fonts
- Pill-shape buttons (pills are for nav tags only)
- Hover lift above 1px
- Animations on text content (only on cards / nav)
- Hardcoded hex outside `:root`
- `git add .` / `git add -A` (per-file add is mandatory)
- Direct use of `#4a8cff` in component CSS (use `var(--accent)`)

## 4 extracted taste principles

1. **Hero-Scale Title as Commitment Signal** — 80px/800 typographic hero = "decide in 3 seconds"
2. **Dark Glassmorphic Cards Over Flat Boxes** — blue tint + blue glow
3. **Single Accent Color as Signal, Not Shade** — blue dominant, orange scarcity
4. **Restraint: No Hero Image** — the essay's value is intellectual, not emotional

## When in doubt

Read `docs/taste-rules.md` (repo root) for the full rationale. If a change doesn't fit any of the 4 documented principles, propose it as a separate design review — not a silent code change.
